it was.

532
00:19:04,776 --> 00:19:07,646
So... just what were you expecting

533
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:09,047
when you went over there?

534
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:13,952
Daphne. Right on time.

535
00:19:14,453 --> 00:19:15,454
I'm glad you're here.

536
00:19:15,454 --> 00:19:16,455
Come in.

537
00:19:17,456 --> 00:19:20,459
Let me, uh, take your coat.

538
00:19:20,459 --> 00:19:22,461
I brought the recipe.

539
00:19:22,461 --> 00:19:23,962
Hmm?

540
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:26,965
Oh, uh, uh, for, uh,
sticky toffee pudding.

541
00:19:26,965 --> 00:19:28,467
Mm, mm, mm.

542
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,936
Well, that's why I'm here, isn't it?

543
00:19:30,936 --> 00:19:33,438
To teach you to make it?

544
00:19:33,438 --> 00:19:35,440
Yes.

545
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,210
You're not buying it, are you?

546
00:19:38,210 --> 00:19:40,412
No, not really.

547
00:19:40,412 --> 00:19:42,748
So, uh...

548
00:19:42,748 --> 00:19:44,750
you know why I asked you here tonight?

549
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,652
I think I do.

550
00:19:46,652 --> 00:19:49,054
I mean, when a man
asks you to his house

551
00:19:49,555 --> 00:19:52,491
to make pudding on a
Saturday night, you...

552
00:19:52,491 --> 00:19:54,760
Pretty flimsy excuse, wasn't it?

553
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,895
Well, it got me here.

554
00:19:56,895 --> 00:19:59,064
Well, I'm glad.

555
00:20:00,432 --> 00:20:01,900
Make yourself comfortable.

556
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:04,870
All right.

557
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:12,177
ALL: Surprise!

558
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:15,080
DONNY: Welcome to your shower, honey.

559
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:16,715
(laughing)

560
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,050
Oh, my God, you're trembling.

561
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:20,552
Yes, well... I'm
absolutely blown away.

562
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:21,820
Oh, come on, Daphne,

563
00:20:21,820 --> 00:20:23,121
you were on to us.

564
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:26,625
No, really... you had
me completely fooled.

565
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:28,627
(others laughing)

566
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:32,130
My God...

567
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:34,066
Dr. Crane...

568
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:36,001
You know, it might be time

569
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:38,403
to start calling him "Niles."

570
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:42,341
This is so confusing.

571
00:20:42,341 --> 00:20:43,842
I mean, what about Donny?

572
00:20:43,842 --> 00:20:45,310
He's the man I love.

573
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:47,546
Are you sure about that?

574
00:20:51,617 --> 00:20:54,620
No.

575
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:57,623
Oh, I have so many questions.

576
00:20:57,623 --> 00:21:00,559
What does this mean?
What do I do?

577
00:21:02,494 --> 00:21:06,965
I'm sorry, but our time is up.

578
00:21:18,710 --> 00:21:20,712
♪ Hey, baby, I hear the blues
a'callin' ♪

579
00:21:20,712 --> 00:21:23,715
♪ Tossed salads and scrambled eggs ♪

580
00:21:23,715 --> 00:21:25,517
♪ Oh, my ♪

581
00:21:25,517 --> 00:21:28,320
♪ And maybe I seem a bit confused ♪

582
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,789
♪ Yeah, maybe, but I got you pegged ♪

583
00:21:30,789 --> 00:21:32,691
(laughing)

584
00:21:32,691 --> 00:21:34,660
♪ But I don't know what to do ♪

585
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:39,164
♪ With those tossed salads
and scrambled eggs ♪

586
00:21:39,164 --> 00:21:42,134
♪ They're callin' again. ♪

587
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:45,137
Scrambled eggs all over my face.

588
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,973
What is a boy to do?

589
00:21:49,408 --> 00:21:52,711
Frasier has left the building.

